The USDA signed a waiver to extend the Summer Feeding Program that provides any child age birth to 18 years a ‚ÄúGrab and Go meal. They do not need to live in the Harrison School District or attend D2 schools.

This service to the community will occur at 5 schools through October as a drive-thru event. Meals will be served from 11:30 a.m. - 12:30 p.m. Children do not have to be in the vehicle with adults, but staff will ask for the child‚Äôs name.

‚ÄúGrab and Go‚Äù Meal Locations:
* Centennial Elementary School
* Pikes Peak Elementary School
* Soaring Eagles Elementary School
* Fox Meadow Middle School
* Sierra High School

post_text:
NEW COVID-19 GUIDELINES FOR STAFF AND PARENTS - 8/17/2020

Last week Colorado‚Äôs Department of Health and Environment issued new guidelines for return to school/work. The new guidelines allow students and staff to safely return to school much quicker than what was previously required. Under the new guidelines, students and staff can return to school or work, if they meet the Criteria to Return to Care or In-Person Learning below:

All major symptoms have resolved for 24 hours; or
All minor symptoms have resolved for 48 hours; or
Alternate medical diagnosis explaining the symptoms; or
A negative COVID-19 PCR test; or
14 days have passed since the student or staff member(s) sent home was last in school.

To read the full update, please click here for more information -- https://www.hsd2.org/domain/1824

Summer break is an excellent time for students 14 ¬Ω and older to start taking classes for a Colorado permit. Proper preparation prepares your teen to make the decisions necessary to drive safely and confidently for life.

During this COVID-19 Crisis you have two great options! LIVE ONLINE (using Zoom) or SELF-PACED ONLINE. The current cost of this course is $199 ‚Äì but for HSD2 students it is only $99! This course is like being in the classroom, with the ability to interact and ask questions of the instructor, take quizzes and more. Flexible dates and times are available. Student must be 14 ¬Ω to begin the course.

Call 720-496-2247 to register or register online at https://hsd2.bedrivingus.com/enroll

** Students over 16 may enroll in the untimed Express Colorado Driver‚Äôs Ed Course. **

The Summer Adventure game presented by Children‚Äôs Hospital of Colorado helps kids and teens stay engaged and active over the summer months, despite the COVID-19 pandemic.

Summer break is an excellent time for students 14 ¬Ω and older to start taking classes for a Colorado permit. Proper preparation prepares your teen to make the decisions necessary to drive safely and confidently for life.

During this COVID-19 Crisis you have two great options! LIVE ONLINE (using Zoom) or SELF-PACED ONLINE. The current cost of this course is $199 ‚Äì but for HSD2 students it is only $99! This course is like being in the classroom, with the ability to interact and ask questions of the instructor, take quizzes and more. Flexible dates and times are available. Student must be 14 ¬Ω to begin the course.

Call 720-496-2247 to register or register online at https://hsd2.bedrivingus.com/enroll

** Students over 16 may enroll in the untimed Express Colorado Driver‚Äôs Ed Course. **

post_text: Does your child receive free or reduced-price school meals during the school year, or do you believe you may now qualify based on a recent income change? Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, can help you feed your family while schools are closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. If you do not currently receive SNAP benefits, apply here for P-EBT today: https://www.colorado.gov/cdhs/p-ebt

Summer break is an excellent time for students 14 ¬Ω and older to start taking classes for a Colorado permit. Proper preparation prepares your teen to make the decisions necessary to drive safely and confidently for life.

During this COVID-19 Crisis you have two great options! LIVE ONLINE (using Zoom) or SELF-PACED ONLINE. The current cost of this course is $199 ‚Äì but for HSD2 students it is only $99! This course is like being in the classroom, with the ability to interact and ask questions of the instructor, take quizzes and more. Flexible dates and times are available. Student must be 14 ¬Ω to begin the course.

Call 720-496-2247 to register or register online at https://hsd2.bedrivingus.com/enroll

** Students over 16 may enroll in the untimed Express Colorado Driver‚Äôs Ed Course. **

The United States Air Force Academy are asking our district students to join other city district students and our city‚Äôs civic leaders to extend a big welcome to the Academy‚Äôs Class of 2024 by participating in USAFA‚Äôs online social media welcome campaign - so that the incoming cadets ‚Äúfeel the love‚Äù and know they are recognized for the service they are about to give to our nation.

‚Ä¢ Either print out and color in the attached template or create a sign of your own. The template allows room for each artist to add something original below the heading.

post_text: Does your child receive free or reduced-price school meals during the school year, or do you believe you may now qualify based on a recent income change? Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, can help you feed your family while schools are closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. If you do not currently receive SNAP benefits, apply here for P-EBT today: https://www.colorado.gov/cdhs/p-ebt

Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, can help you feed your family while schools are closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. Summer break is an excellent time for students 14 ¬Ω and older to start taking classes for a Colorado permit. Proper preparation prepares your teen to make the decisions necessary to drive safely and confidently for life.

During this COVID-19 Crisis you have two great options! LIVE ONLINE (using Zoom) or SELF-PACED ONLINE. The current cost of this course is $199 ‚Äì but for HSD2 students it is only $99! This course is like being in the classroom, with the ability to interact and ask questions of the instructor, take quizzes and more. Flexible dates and times are available. Student must be 14 ¬Ω to begin the course.

Call 720-496-2247 to register or register online at https://hsd2.bedrivingus.com/enroll

** Students over 16 may enroll in the untimed Express Colorado Driver‚Äôs Ed Course. **

Lynda Idle, CLDE Director, Recognized with the 2020 Distinguished Administrator Award by CDE!

The Culturally and Linguistically Diverse Education (CLDE) office wishes to congratulate Lynda Espinoza Idle from Harrison School District 2 who was chosen as the winner of the 2020 Distinguished Administrator in Support of Culturally and Linguistically Diverse Learners Award. The award is presented annually to one distinguished administrator who has demonstrated excellence in creating successful outcomes by supporting the academic, linguistic, and social-emotional needs of culturally and linguistically diverse learners and their families. The CLDE office has honored administrators and educators who have demonstrated excellence in their work with culturally and linguistically diverse learners since 2007.

Congratulations, Lynda!
